## Glob Pattern Examples
The following describe where rules and instructions can act on generally within a code repository.

Common glob patterns for different rule types:
- Core standards: .cursor/rules/core/*.mdc
- Util standards: .cursor/rules/utils/*.mdc
- Static assets: public/**, assets/**/*(.png|.gif|.webp|.avif|.jpeg|.jpg),
- Linting: eslintrc.json, .eslintrc, eslint.js, .prettierrc, prettier.json
- Configuration files: **.config.(ts|js), Makefile
- Testing standards: __test__/**/*.test(.ts|.js), *.test.(js|ts|tsx), *.spec.ts
- Testing Cursor rules: test-**.mdc
- React components: src/components/**/*.tsx
- Vue components: src/components/**/*.vue
- Documentation: docs/**/*.md, *.md
- Github actions: .github/**/*.yml
- Multiple extensions: *.js, *.ts, *.tsx
- Multiple patterns: dist/**/*.*, docs/**/*.md, *test*.*